t;font-size:17px;line-height:1.6!important;text-align:left;letter-spacing:-=
0.007em!important">The main reason I wanted to sell is that there&#39;s a h=
uge difference between being a starter and being an operator. A starter has=
 the vision to create a product or business from nothing, and build it out.=
 The skillset here is mostly creativity, vision and assuming at least some =
risk. An operator, on the other hand, has the ability to run an existing th=
ing on a daily basis. The skill set required is mostly process optimization=
, support, and steering.</p>

<p dir=3D"ltr" style=3D"margin:10px 0;padding:0;margin-bottom:20px;color:#1=
11!important;font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,San Francisco,Hel=
vetica Neue,Helvetica,Ubuntu,Roboto,Noto,Segoe UI,Arial,sans-serif!importan=
t;font-size:17px;line-height:1.6!important;text-align:left;letter-spacing:-=
0.007em!important">I think I fall more in the starter than operator camp, e=
